The _taktil_ noun pattern: The _taktil_ noun pattern is one of the [[Hebrew noun patterns]] and produces words such as:
| *Shoresh* | *_Hif’il_ Verb* | *_Pi’el_ Noun* |
| בשׁל <br> cooking | בִּשֵּׁל (_bish’sheil_) <br> he cooked | תַּבְשִׁיל (_tavshil_) <br> a cooked item |
| פקד <br> managing | הִפְקִיד (_hifkid_) <br> he entrusted | תַּפְקִיד (_tafkid_) <br> order, commanded duty |
| רגל <br> routine | הִרְגִּיל (_hirg’gil_) <br> he habituated | תַּרְגִּיל (_targ’gil_) <br> practice |
Nouns in the _taktil_ noun pattern come from [[_hif’il_]] verbs. More examples of words in the _kittul_ noun pattern [can be found on Pealim](https://www.pealim.com/dict/?pos=noun&nm=taqtil).
